title: ROUNDUP: Warriors lose in first round of Class A sectional
text:
by Kevin Harris 
FERDINAND — The Christian Academy girls’ soccer team’s season came to an end Monday evening in a 4-0 loss to Heritage Hills in the first round of the Class A Forest Park Sectional. The Warriors were ranked 19th in the final Indiana Soccer Coaches Association Class A poll. 
No other details of the game were reported at press time. 
The sectional will continue at 6 tonight as Class A No. 8 Providence will face No. 17 North Harrison. The winner will play in the semifinals against the victor of tonight’s second game between Salem and Northeast Dubois at about 7:45 p.m. Thursday at Forest Park. 
The Pioneers are back in Class A this year after spending the last two seasons in Class 2A. They won the Class 2A Floyd Central Sectional last year. Providence captured the first-ever Class A state championship in 2011. The Pioneers were Class A state runners-up in 2012. 
LATE SATURDAY RESULTS 
GIRLS’ GOLF 
INGRAM 39TH, SEATON 48TH AT STATE 
CARMEL — Floyd Central senior Jessica Ingram and Silver Creek senior Charlotte Seaton each competed in the IHSAA State Finals last weekend at Prairie View Golf Club. 
Ingram wound up in a four-way tie for 39th with a two-round score of 174 (30-over-par). Ingram shot an 86 in last Friday’s first round, followed by an 88 last Saturday. 
Seaton finished in a four-way tie for 48th with a 177 (33-over). Seaton fired a 90 in the first round and an 87 in the second and final round. Seaton has given a verbal commitment to play at Bellarmine next season. 
Evansville North, which won the Washington Regional, repeated as team state champions. Lake Central sophomore Alexis Miestowski was the state medalist with a 145 (1-over).
